content: People I know keep popping up as having "Joined Telegram!" while it's NOT them but someone using a very old number they no longer have & those numbers aren't even associated with them anymore in my contact info for themâ€”so why the heck is this happening? This is a HUGE SOCIAL ENGINEERING SECURITY HOLE as the app simply doesn't verify your contacts. EDIT: thanks for the tone deaf response.
replyContent: Hello, note that the new owner of a recycled phone number would not know what name you see them as, because it's based on the name you saved the contact as on your end. So if the contact phone number / name is outdated, it can unfortunately create confusion for both sides. Deleting the synced contacts can help refresh your contacts list.

replyContent: By default, Telegram sends new login codes to a userâ€™s other active *Telegram apps* when a user is logged in on multiple devices. On the mobile apps, there is the option to request an SMS code instead â€“ from â€˜Send as SMSâ€™ on the login page. For security reasons, the Web and Desktop apps canâ€™t send SMS codes, only login codes to other Telegram apps.

replyContent: Hello, if you receive a contact join notification, the name is based on the contact saved in your Contacts app. If the phone number was recycled to a new owner, it won't show the new owner's name, only the old contact name. You can go to Telegram Settings > Privacy and Security > Delete Synced Contacts, then re-sync contacts.

replyContent: Hello, note that you can set who can see your last seen in Telegram Settings > Privacy and Security > Last Seen & Online. If disabled, approximate last seen values are used instead (last seen recently, last seen a long time ago, etc). This helps keep stalkers away but makes it easy to see whether a person is reachable over Telegram.

replyContent: We apologize for this experience. Make sure to go to Telegram Settings > Devices > Terminate All Other Sessions. Then log out of your last session to reset all of your keys. replyContent: That sounds like a very frustrating situation. You can go to Telegram Settings > Privacy and Security > Phone Number, set that to Nobody, then a new setting will appear. Set the new setting to "My Contacts", then people can't add you by phone number if you don't have them as a contact. You can also disable your username and Forwarded Messages.
